&lt;h2 class="relative group"&gt;Why Visit Dubrovnik?
 &lt;div id="why-visit-dubrovnik" class="anchor"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
 
 &lt;span
 class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none"&gt;
 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#why-visit-dubrovnik" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://cruise.techpawz.com/posts/dubrovnik_shore-excursions/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;Dubrovnik&lt;/a&gt;, often referred to as the &amp;ldquo;Pearl of the Adriatic,&amp;rdquo; is a stunning coastal city that has captivated travelers for centuries. With its terracotta rooftops, ancient city walls, and crystal-clear waters, Dubrovnik is a visual feast that combines rich history with breathtaking natural beauty. The city is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and boasts a well-preserved medieval old town that transports visitors back in time. Walking along the famous Stradun, the main thoroughfare, you&amp;rsquo;ll find charming shops, vibrant street performances, and the warm hospitality of the locals.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>